In a bid to boost staff efficiency, Sifax Group has trained a total of 101 staff in different areas from various subsidiaries of the organization in the first quarter of 2022. The training focused on the basic needs of the staff, including leadership competence, operations management, terminal traffic management, health, safety & environment, security, digital marketing, and corporate governance. In a statement in Lagos, the Group Head, Corporate Communications, Sifax Group, Muyiwa Akande, explained that selected traffic managers from Ports and Cargo Handling Services, a subsidiary of SIFAX Group, were trained on terminal traffic management. According to him, the one-week training was aimed at providing attendees with practical skills that would enable them to effectively and efficiently coordinate the movement of people, vehicles, and equipment within the terminal. â€œOperations staff from the same subsidiary were trained on current terminal operational skills, as well as an understanding of the importance of standards, robust processes and procedures and analysing the different elements of container terminal operations especially in understanding the full operational cycle of the ship, yard and gate activities.  Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com